# WordPress Global Guardrails

- Build for WordPress conventions first; avoid custom architecture unless necessary.
- Keep changes small and scoped to the request; do not refactor unrelated code.
- Never edit WordPress core files or vendor code directly.
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or environment-specific paths.
- Prefer reusable helpers and hooks over duplicated logic.
- Keep functions focused and readable; split large functions into smaller units.
- Handle failure paths explicitly and return safe fallbacks.
- Preserve backward compatibility unless the task explicitly allows breaking changes.
- Document non-obvious decisions briefly, focusing on why.
